# gen160 E1: social composition over FRESH vocab (thora/parrot/kiwi).
# One conversation forces six subsystems to cooperate: social register
# (greeting), personal name memory, personal possession memory, KB fact intake,
# discourse reference (pronoun "it" bound to the last subject), and the personal
# summary. The follow-up questions read back what earlier turns stored.
#subsystems: social-register, name-memory, possession-memory, fact-intake, discourse-reference, personal-summary
#expect: pass
#class: composes-unchanged
> hey
< hi there
> my name is thora
< nice to meet you thora
> i have a parrot named kiwi
< your parrot is called kiwi
> kiwi is a bird
< learned birdkiwi
> is it a bird?
< yes
> what is my parrot called?
< kiwi
> what is my name?
< your name is thora
> what do you remember about me?
< your name is thora your parrot is kiwi